HEADWORD: Saiga
<hw>Sai"ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>saika</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An antelope (<spn>Saiga
Tartarica</spn>) native of the plains of Siberia and Eastern Russia. The
male has erect annulated horns, and tufts of long hair beneath the eyes
and ears.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

